Asymptotic notation & Xendo

$\Theta, O, \Omega, o, \omega$ are sets of functions given by $\theta'(f(n))$ for some $f(n)$ with $\theta' \in \{ \Theta, O, \Omega, o, \omega \}$

$\Theta$ is a tight bound;
$O$ is an upper bound;
$\Omega$ is a lower bound.

$o$ is a strict upper bound ($f \in o \implies f \not\in O$)
$\omega$ is a strict lower bound ($f \in \omega \implies f \not\in \Omega$)

cf. Worksheets
